$$\mathcal{I}=\int_{0}^{1}\frac{x\mathbf{K}^2\left ( x \right )}{\sqrt{1-x^{2}}}\mathrm{d}x=\frac{\pi ^{4}}{16}\,_7F_6\left ( 
\dfrac{1}{2},\dfrac{1}{2},\dfrac{1}{2},\dfrac{1}{2},\dfrac{1}{2},\dfrac{1}{2},\dfrac{5}{4};\dfrac{1}{4},1,1,1,1,1;1 \right ).$$
